h) of Accra.\n| Metropolitan Emmanuel (Kagias) of Ptolemaidos.\n| Metropolitan Gregorios (Stergiou) of Cameroon and Exarch of Central Africa.\n| Metropolitan Nicodemos (Priangellos) of Memphis.\n| Metropolitan Meletios (Kamiloudes) of Katanga.\n| Bishop Panteleimon (Arathymos) of Brazzaville and Gabon.\n| Bishop Innokentios (Biakatonta) of Burudi and Rwanda.\n| Bishop Crysostomos (Karagounis) of Mozambique.\n| Bishop Neofytos (Kongai) of Nyeri and Mount Kenya.\n| '''Special Consultants''':\n:* Dr. Panagiotis Tzoumerkas, Professor, University Ecclesiastical Academy of Thessaloniki.\n:* Archimandrite Paisios (Larentzakis).\n:* Archimandrite Peter (Parginos).\n:* Protopresbyter Athenodoros Papaevropiadis.\n:* Protopresbyter Joseph Kwame Labi Ayete.\n:* Deacon Emmanuel Kamanua.\n}}\n\n{{Collapsible list\n| title=Church of Jerusalem\n| bullets\t=\ton\n| Patriarch [[Patriarch Theophilos III of Jerusalem|Theophilos (Giannopoulos) III]], of Jerusalem.<ref name=FREIBURG/> \n| Metropolitan [[orthodoxwiki:Benedict (Tsekouras) of Philadelphia|Benedict (Tsekouras) of Philadelphia]].\n| Archbishop Aristarchos (Peristeris) of Constantina.\n| Archbishop Theophylaktos (Georgiadis) of Jordan.\n| Archbishop Nektarios (Selalmadzidis) of Anthedon.\n| Archbishop Philoumenos (Machamre) of Pella.\n| '''Special Consultants''':\n:* Archimandrite Christophoros (Mousa).\n:* Archimandrite Damianos (Panou).\n:* Archimandrite Nikodemos (Skrettas).\n:* Archimandrite Chrysostomos (Nasis).\n:* Archimandrite Ieronymos (Delioglou).\n:* Protopresbyter [[George Dragas|Georgios Dragas]].\n:* Professor Theodoros Yiangou.<ref>''[http://www.jp-newsgate.net/en/2016/06/16/24394 THE PATRIARCHATE\u2019S PARTICIPATION IN THE DELIBERATIONS OF THE GREAT SYNOD OF ORTHODOX CHURCHES \u2013 ARRIVAL IN CHANIA].'' The Patriarchate of Jerusalem - Official News Gate. 16/06/2016.</ref>\n}}\n\n{{Collapsible list\n| title = Serbian Orthodox Church\n| On June 9, 2016, the Serbian Orthodox Church joined a number of local Churches which did not consider participation in the Pan-Orthodox Council slated for late June on Crete to be possible.<ref>[http://www.interfax-religion.com/?act=news&div=13008 Serbian Orthodox Church refuses to participate in Pan-Orthodox Council]. Interfax-Religion. 09 June 2016, 12:37.</ref> However on June 15, 2016, the Serbian Church changed its position on the issue of its participation in the Pan-Orthodox Council and decided to attend,<ref>[http://interfax-religion.com/?act=news&div=13027 Serbian Church changes its decision not to take part in Pan-Orthodox Council]. Interfax-Religion. 15 June 2016, 15:52</ref> with the caveat that it reserved the right to leave forum on Crete if the position of those churches who refused to participate was ignored.<ref>[http://interfax-religion.com/?act=news&div=13029 Serbian Church says will leave forum on Crete if position of those who refused to participate in it is ignored]. Interfax-Religion. 15 June 2016, 16:58.</ref>\n* Serbian Patriarch [[Patriarch Irinej of Serbia|Irinej (Gavrilovi\u0107)]], the Archbishop of [[Pe\u0107]], Metropolitan of [[Belgrade]] and [[Sremski Karlovci|Karlovci]].<ref name=FREIBURG/> \n* Archbishop [[Archbishop Jovan VI of Ohrid|Jovan VI (Vrani\u0161kovski)]] of [[Orthodox Ohrid Archbishopric|Ohrid and Skopje]].\n* Metropolitan [[Amfilohije Radovi\u0107|Amfilohije (Radovi\u0107)]] of [[Metropolitanate of Montenegro and the Littoral|Montenegro and the Littoral]].\n* Metropolitan [[Porfirije Peri\u0107|Porfirije (Peri\u0107)]] of [[Metropolitanate of Zagreb and Ljubljana|Zagreb and Ljubljana]].\n* Bishop Vasilije (Vadi\u0107) of [[Eparchy of Srem|Sirmium]].\n* Bishop Lukijan (Panteli\u0107) of [[Eparchy of Buda|Budim]].\n* Bishop Longin (Kr\u010do) of [[Diocese of New Gracanica \u2013 Midwestern America|Nova Gracanica]].\n* Bishop [[Irinej Bulovi\u0107|Irinej (Bulovi\u0107)]] of [[Eparchy of Ba\u010dka|Ba\u010dka]].\n* Bishop Hrizostom (Jevi\u0107) of Zvornik and Tuzla.\n* Bishop Justin (Stefanovi\u0107) of [[Eparchy of \u017di\u010da|Zica]].\n* Bishop Pahomije (Ga\u010di\u0107) of Vranje.\n* Bishop Jovan (Mladenovi\u0107) of Sumadija.\n* Bishop [[Ignatije Midi\u0107|Ignatije (Midi\u0107)]] of [[Eparchy of Brani\u010devo|Branicevo]].\n* Bishop Fotije (Sladojevi\u0107) of [[Eparchy of Dalmatia|Dalmatia]].\n* Bishop Atanasije (Rakita) of Bihac and Petrovac.\n* Bishop Joanikije (Mi\u0107ovi\u0107) of [[Eparchy of Budimlja and Nik\u0161i\u0107|Niksic and Budimlje]].\n* Bishop Grigorije (Duri\u0107) of [[Eparchy of Zahumlje and Herzegovina|Zahumlje and Hercegovina]].\n* Bishop Milutin (Kne\u017eevi\u0107) of Valjevo.\n* Bishop Maxim (Vasiljevi\u0107) in [[Serbian Orthodox Eparchy of Western America|Western America]].\n* Bishop Irinej (Dobrijevi\u0107) in [[Serbian Orthodox Eparchy of Australia and New Zealand|Australia and New Zealand]].\n* Bishop David (Perovi\u0107) of Krusevac.\n* Bishop Jovan (\u0106ulibrk) of [[Eparchy of Slavonia|Slavonija]].\n* Bishop Andrej (\u0106ilerd\u017ei\u0107) in Austria and Switzerland.\n* Bishop Sergej (Karanovi\u0107) of [[Serbian Orthodox Eparchy of Frankfurt and all of Germany|Frankfurt and all of Germany]].\n* Bishop Ilarion (Golubovi\u0107) of Timok.\n* '''Special Consultants''':\n:* Bishop Jerome (Mo\u010devi\u0107) of Jegar ('''[[:sr:\u0415\u043f\u0438\u0441\u043a\u043e\u043f \u0458\u0435\u0433\u0430\u0440\u0441\u043a\u0438|sr]]''').\n:* Archimandrite Sava (Janjic), of the [[Visoki De\u010dani]] monastery.\n:* Archimandrite Nicodemus (Kosovits), of the [[Krka monastery]].\n:* Protopresbyter-Staurophor Dr. Zoran Krstic.\n:* Protopresbyter Gaja Gajic.\n:* Mr. Vladan Tatalovi\u0107, Assistant Professor at Faculty of Orthodox Theology, Belgrade University.<ref name=\"HOLYCOUNCIL-DELGATES2016\"/>\n}}\n\n{{Collapsible list\n| title=Church of Romania\n| bullets\t=\ton\n| Patriarch [[Patriarch Daniel of Romania|Daniel (Ciobotea)]], of the Romanian Orthodox Church.\n| Archbishop [[:ro:Teofan Savu|Teofan (Savu)]], of Ia\u015fi, and [[Metropolis of Moldavia and Bukovina|Metropolitan of Moldavia and Bucovina]].\n| Archbishop [[Lauren\u021biu Streza|Lauren\u0163iu (Streza)]], of Sibiu, and Metropolitan of [[Transylvania]].\n| Archbishop [[:ro:Andrei Andreicu\u021b|Andrei (Andreicu\u021b)]], of Vad, Feleacu and Cluj, and Metropolitan of [[Cluj County|Cluj]], [[Maramure\u0219]] and S\u0103laj.\n| Archbishop [[:ro:Irineu Popa|Irineu (Popa)]], of Craiova, and Metropolitan of Oltenia.\n| Archbishop [[:ro:Ioan Selejan|Ioan (Selejan)]], of Timi\u015foara, and Metropolitan of Banat.\n| Archbishop [[:ro:Iosif Pop|Iosif (Pop)]], of Western Europe, and Metropolitan of Western and Southern Europe.\n| Archbishop [[:ro:Serafim Joant\u0103|Serafim (Joant\u0103)]], of Germany, Austria and Luxembourg, and Metropolitan of Germany, Central and Northern Europe.\n| Archbishop Nifon (Mih\u0103i\u0163\u0103), Metropolitan of [[T\u00e2rgovi\u0219te]].\n| Archbishop Irineu (Pop) of [[Alba Iulia]].\n| Archbishop Varsanufie (Gogescu) of R\u00e2mnic.\n| Archbishop Ioachim (Giosanu) of [[Roman, Romania|Roman]] and [[Bac\u0103u]].\n| Archbishop [[:ro:Casian Cr\u0103ciun|Casian (Cr\u0103ciun)]] of Lower Danube.\n| Archbishop [[Timotei (Seviciu)]] of [[Archdiocese of Arad|Arad]].\n| Archbishop [[:ro:Nicolae Condrea|Nicolae (Condrea)]] in the [[Romanian Orthodox Archdiocese of America and Canada|Americas]].\n| Bishop [[:ro:Sofronie Drincec|Sofronie (Drincec)]] of [[Oradea]].\n| Bishop Nicodim (Nicol\u0103escu) of [[Cara\u0219-Severin County|Severin]] and [[Strehaia]].\n| Bishop [[:ro:Visarion B\u0103l\u021bat|Visarion (B\u0103l\u021bat)]] of [[Tulcea]].\n| Bishop Petroniu (Florea) of [[S\u0103laj County|S\u0103laj]].\n| Bishop [[Siluan M\u0103nuil\u0103|Siluan (M\u0103nuil\u0103)]] of Hungary.\n| Bishop Siluan (\u015epan) of Italy.\n| Bishop Timotei (Lauran) of Spain and Portugal.\n| Bishop Macarie (Dr\u0103goi) of Northern Europe.\n| Bishop Varlaam (Merticariu) of [[Ploie\u0219ti]], Assistant Bishop to the Patriarch, Secretary of the Holy Council.\n| Bishop Emilian (Nica) of Lovi\u015fte, Assistant Bishop to the Archdiocese of R\u00e2mnic.<ref name=FREIBURG/><ref name=HOLYCOUNCIL-DELGATES2016/>\n}}\n\n{{Collapsible list\n| title=Church of Cyprus\n| bullets\t=\ton\n| Archbishop [[Chrysostomos II of Cyprus|Chrysostomos II (Dimitriou)]] of Nova Justiniana and All Cyprus.<ref name=FREIBURG/><ref name=HOLYCOUNCIL-DELGATES2016/> \n| Metropolitan Georgios (Papachrysostomou) of [[Paphos]] and [[Exarchate]] of [[Arsinoe (Southwest Cyprus)|Arsinoe]] and [[Petra Tou Romiou|Romaeon]].\n| Metropolitan Chrysostomos (Mahairiotis) of [[Kition]] and [[Exarchate]] of [[Larnaca]] and [[Pano Lefkara]].\n| Metropolitan Chrysostomos (Kykkotis) of [[Kyrenia]] and [[Exarchate]] of [[Lapithos]] and [[Karavas]].\n| Metropolitan Athanasios (Nikolaou) of [[Limassol]], [[Amathous]] and [[Kourion]].\n| Metropolitan Neophytos (Masouras) of [[Morphou]] and [[Soli, Cyprus|Soloi]].\n| Metropolitan Vasileios (Karajiannis) of [[Salamis, Cyprus|Constantia]] and [[Famagusta|Ammochostos]].\n| Metropolitan Nikiphoros (Kykkotis) of [[Kykkos Monastery|Kykkos]] and Tillyria.\n| Metropolitan Isa\u00efas (Kykkotis) of [[Tamassos]] and [[Pera Orinis|Oreini]].\n| Metropolitan Barnabas  (Stavrovouniotis) of [[Tremetousia|Tremithousa]] and Lefkara.\n| Bishop Christophoros (Tsiakkas) of [[Karpasia (town)|Karpasion]].\n| Bishop Nektarios (Spyrou) of [[Arsinoe (Southwest Cyprus)|Arsinoe]].\n| Bishop Nikolaos (Timiadis) of [[Amathus]].\n| Bishop Epiphanios (Mahairiotis) of [[Ledra]].\n| Bishop Leontios (Englistriotis) of [[Kythrea|Chytron]].\n| Bishop Porphyrios (Mahairiotis) of [[Yeni\u015fehir, Nicosia|Neapolis]].\n| Bishop Gregory (Hatziouraniou) of [[Mesaoria]].\n| '''Special Consultants''':\n:* Archimandrite Ioannis (Ioannou), Igumen of [http://www.whatson-northcyprus.com/interest/famagusta/salamis/barnabas.htm Monastery of St. Barnabas].\n:* Archimandrite Benedict (Ioannou), Director of St. Barnabas Seminary.\n:* Archimandrite Papagrigorios (Ioannidis).\n:* Archimandrite Gregory (Mousouroulis).\n:* Archimandrite Augustinos (Kkaras).\n:* Deacon Cyprian Kountouris.\n:* Deacon Michael Nicholaou.\n:* Mr. Michael Spyrou, Secretary of the Holy Council.\n}}\n\n{{Collapsible list\n| title=Church of Greece\n| A Greek media report of May 24, 2016 stated that at least a dozen bishops who had been appointed<ref name=GREECE-MAR8>{{in lang|el}} ''[http://www.ecclesia.gr/epikairotita/main_epikairotita_next.asp?id=1735 \u03a0\u03c1\u03ce\u03c4\u03b7 \u03a3\u03c5\u03bd\u03b5\u03b4\u03c1\u03af\u03b1 \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u0399\u03b5\u03c1\u03ac\u03c2 \u03a3\u03c5\u03bd\u03cc\u03b4\u03bf\u03c5 \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u0399\u03b5\u03c1\u03b1\u03c1\u03c7\u03af\u03b1\u03c2 \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u0395\u03ba\u03ba\u03bb\u03b7\u03c3\u03af\u03b1\u03c2 \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03bf\u03c2].'' ECCLESIA.GR. 8.3.2016.</ref> to participate in the Holy and Great Council said that they refused to attend. The specific prelates were to be replaced by other metropolitans at an urgently convened summit of the hierarchy of the Church of Greece.<ref>{{in lang|el}} ''[http://www.proinoslogos.gr/epikairotita/42-koinonia/36474-%CE%B4%CF%8E%CE%B4%CE%B5%CE%BA%CE%B1-%CE%BC%CE%B7%CF%84%CF%81%CE%BF%CF%80%CE%BF%CE%BB%CE%AF%CF%84%CE%B5%CF%82-%CF%80%CE%B1%CF%81%CE%B1%CE%B9%CF%84%CE%BF%CF%8D%CE%BD%CF%84%CE%B1%CE%B9-%CE%B1%CF%80%CF%8C-%CF%84%CE%B7-%CE%BC%CE%B5%CE%B3%CE%AC%CE%BB%CE%B7-%CF%83%CF%8D%CE%BD%CE%BF%CE%B4%CE%BF-%CF%84%CF%89%CE%BD-%CE%BF%CF%81%CE%B8%CE%BF%CE%B4%CF%8C%CE%BE%CF%89%CE%BD \u0394\u03ce\u03b4\u03b5\u03ba\u03b1 \u039c\u03b7\u03c4\u03c1\u03bf\u03c0\u03bf\u03bb\u03af\u03c4\u03b5\u03c2 \u03c0\u03b1\u03c1\u03b1\u03b9\u03c4\u03bf\u03cd\u03bd\u03c4\u03b1\u03b9 \u03b1\u03c0\u03cc \u03c4\u03b7 \u039c\u03b5\u03b3\u03ac\u03bb\u03b7 \u03a3\u03cd\u03bd\u03bf\u03b4\u03bf \u03c4\u03c9\u03bd \u039f\u03c1\u03b8\u03bf\u03b4\u03cc\u03be\u03c9\u03bd].'' \u03a0\u03a1\u03a9\u0399\u039d\u039f\u03a3 \u039b\u039f\u0393\u039f\u03a3. 24 \u039c\u0391\u0399\u039f\u03a3 2016.</ref> The original list of participants was published on March 8, 2016.<ref name=GREECE-MAR8/><ref>{{in lang|el}} ''[http://www.greekamericannewsagency.com/2010-01-19-17-52-24/2010-01-21-18-56-31/45575-megali-synodos-antipro-ekkl-tis-ellados H \u0391\u03bd\u03c4\u03b9\u03c0\u03c1\u03bf\u03c3\u03c9\u03c0\u03b5\u03af\u03b1 \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u0395\u03ba\u03ba\u03bb\u03b7\u03c3\u03af\u03b1\u03c2 \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4o\u03c2 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7 \u039c\u03b5\u03b3\u03ac\u03bb\u03b7 \u03a3\u03cd\u03bd\u03bf\u03b4\u03bf].'' Greek American News Agency. 31 \u039c\u03b1\u0390\u03bf\u03c5 2016.</ref> The final delagtion that attended the Synod included the following:<ref name=HOLYCOUNCIL-DELGATES2016/>\n* Archbishop [[Ieronymos II of Athens|Ieronymos II (Liapis) of Athens]].<ref name=FREIBURG/>\n* Metropolitan Prokopios (Tsakoumakas) of [[Philippi]], [[Kavala|Neapolis]] and [[Thasos]].\n* Metropolitan Chrysostomos (Zaphiris) of [[Peristeri]].\n* Metropolitan Germanos (Paraskevopoulos) of [[Elis]] and [[Oleni]].\n* Metropolitan Alexandros (Papadopoulos) of [[Mantineia]] and [[North Kynouria|Kynouria]].\n* Metropolitan Ignatios (Alexiou) of [[Arta (regional unit)|Arta]].\n* Metropolitan Ignatios (Lappas) of [[Metropolis of Larissa and Tyrnavos|Larissa and Tyrnavos]].\n* Metropolitan Damaskinos (Karpathakis) of [[Didymoteicho]]n and [[Orestias]] and Exarchate of [[Haemus Mons|Haemimontos]].\n* Metropolitan Alexios (Vryonis) of [[Nikaia, Attica|Nikaia]].\n* Metropolitan [[Hierotheos (Vlachos)]] of [[Metropolis of Nafpaktos and Agios Vlasios]].<ref>Met. Hierotheos Vlachos. ''[http://www.pravoslavie.ru/english/94354.htm JUST BEFORE THE HOLY AND GREAT COUNCIL].''  Pravoslavie.Ru (Holy Metropolis of Nafpaktos and Saint Vlassios).  June 16, 2016.</ref>\n* Metropolitan Eusebios (Pistol\u00eds) of [[Samos]] and [[Icaria|Ikaria]].\n* Metropolitan Seraphim (Papak\u00f3stas) of [[Metropolis of Kastoria|Kastoria]] and Exarchate of 