s.\n}}\n\n{{Collapsible list\n| title=Church of Poland\n| bullets\t=\ton\n| Metropolitan [[Sawa (Hrycuniak)]] of Warsaw and All Poland.<ref name=FREIBURG/><ref name=HOLYCOUNCIL-DELGATES2016/> \n| Archbishop Szymon (Roma\u0144czuk) of [[\u0141\u00f3d\u017a]] and [[Pozna\u0144]].\n| Archbishop Jeremiasz (Anchimiuk) of [[Wroc\u0142aw]] and [[Szczecin]].\n| Archbishop Abel (Pop\u0142awski) of [[Lublin]] and [[Che\u0142m]].\n| Archbishop [[:pl:Jakub (Kostiuczuk)|Jakub (Kostiuczuk)]] of [[Bia\u0142ystok]] and [[Gda\u0144sk]].\n| Bishop Jerzy (Pa\u0144kowski) of [[Siemiatycze]].\n| Bishop Paisjusz (Martyniuk) of [[Gorlice]].\n| '''Special Consultants''':\n:* Archimandrite Andreas.\n:* Archpriest Anatol Szymaniuk.\n:* Archpriest Andrzej Ku\u017ama.\n:* Archdeacon Pawe\u0142 Tokajuk.\n:* Mr. Jaros\u0142aw Charkiewicz, journalist.\n:* Mr. Jerzy Betlejko, interpreter.\n:* Mr. Miko\u0142aj Podolec, interpreter, steward.\n}}\n\n{{Collapsible list\n| title=Church of Albania\n| bullets\t=\ton\n| Archbishop [[Anastasios of Albania|Anastasios (Yannoulatos)]] of [[Archbishop of Tirana|Tirana, Durres and All Albania]].<ref name=FREIBURG/><ref name=HOLYCOUNCIL-DELGATES2016/><ref>''[http://orthodoxalbania.org/alb/index.php/al/lajme/sinodi-i-shenjte-dhe-i-madh/delegacioni-i-kishes-orthodhokse-autoqefale-te-shqiperise-per-sinodin-e-shenjte-dhe-te-madh Delegacioni i Kish\u00ebs Orthodhokse Autoqefale t\u00eb Shqip\u00ebris\u00eb p\u00ebr Sinodin e Shenjt\u00eb dhe t\u00eb Madh].'' Orthodox Autocephalous Church of Albania. Enjte, 09 Qershor 2016 17:49.</ref>\n| Metropolitan Ignatios (Triantis) of [[Berat]], [[Vlor\u00eb]] and [[Kanin\u00eb|Kanina]].\n| Metropolitan Joan (Pellushi) of [[Kor\u00e7\u00eb|Koritsa]].\n| Metropolitan Demetrios (Ntigkbasanis) of [[Gjirokast\u00ebr|Argyrokastron]].\n| Metropolitan Nikolla (Hyka) of [[Apollonia, Illyria|Apollonia]] and [[Fier]].\n| Metropolitan Andon (Merdani) of [[Elbasan County|Elbasan, Shpat and Librazhd]].\n| Metropolitan Nathaniel (Stergiou) of [[Amantia]].\n| Bishop Asti (Bakallbashi) of [[Byllis]].\n| '''Special Consultants''':\n:* Protopresbyter Jani Trebicka.\n:* Father Anastasios Bendo.\n:* Nun Rakela Dervishi.\n:* Mr. Piro Kondili.\n:* Dr. Dion (Vasil) Tushi.\n:* Mrs. Sonila R\u00ebmbeci (former member of the Presidency, and of the Central Council of the [[Conference of European Churches|CEC]], 2009-2013).\n:* Mr. Orfea Beci (Press Office).\n:* Father Charalampos Gkiokas (Staff of the Archbishop).\n:* Deacon Spiros Topanxha (Staff of the Archbishop).\n}}\n\n{{Collapsible list\n| title=Church of Czech Lands and Slovakia\n| bullets\t=\ton\n| Archbishop [[:cs:Rastislav (arcibiskup)|Rastislav]] (Gont) of [[Pre\u0161ov]], the [[Czech Republic|Czech Lands]] and [[Slovakia]].<ref name=FREIBURG/><ref name=HOLYCOUNCIL-DELGATES2016/><ref>''[http://basilica.ro/en/metropolitan-rastislav-of-czech-lands-and-slovakia-on-first-irenic-visit-to-constantinople/ Metropolitan Rastislav of Czech Lands and Slovakia, on first irenic visit to Constantinople].'' Basilica.ro. 17.05.2016.</ref>\n| Archbishop [[:ru:\u041c\u0438\u0445\u0430\u0438\u043b (\u0414\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0430\u0440)|Michal (Dand\u00e1r)]] of [[Prague]].\n| Bishop [[:cs:Izai\u00e1\u0161 (Slaninka)|Isaiah (Slaninka)]] of [[\u0160umperk]].\n| '''Special Consultants''':\n:* Archpriest Milan Gerka, Secretary of the Holy Council.\n:* Archimandrite Seraphim (\u0160emjatovsk\u00fd).\n:* Archpriest Michal \u0160vajko.\n:* Archdeacon Maxim Durila.\n:* Deacon Kiril Sarkissian.\n:* Ms Iveta Stacova (interpreter).\n}}\n{{Div col end}}\n\n===Churches that did not attend===\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n====Church of Antioch====\nThe [[Greek Orthodox Church of Antioch|Antiochian Church]] pulled out due to the dispute over the ecclesiastical jurisdiction of [[Qatar]] that is also claimed by the Patriarchate of Jerusalem.<ref name=\"econo\" >{{cite news|title=Amid shrieking family rows, the Christian east strives to find its voice|url=https://www.economist.com/news/europe/21700651-amid-shrieking-family-rows-christian-east-strives-find-its-voice-autumn|accessdate=18 June 2016|work=[[The Economist]]|date=18 June 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe Antiochian Church joined the Church of Georgia in their reservations toward the pre-conciliar document about marriage, and also disagreed with the document about the Orthodox diaspora. There were other matters which the Antiochian Church desired to discuss, such as the calendar issue, but had been removed from the agenda due to lack of consensus on the issue.<ref name=\"antiochsynod1\">{{cite web|title=Statement of the Secretariat of the Antiochian Holy Synod, on the 6th of June 2016|url=http://antiochpatriarchate.org/en/page/statement-of-the-secretariat-of-the-antiochian-holy-synod-on-the-6th-of-june-2016/1436/|website=Greek Orthodox Patriarchate of Antioch and All the East|accessdate=7 November 2017}}</ref>\n\nStill desiring to convene a Pan-Orthodox Council with full participation, the Antiochian Church considers the 2016 meeting to be \"a preliminary meeting towards the Pan-Orthodox Council, [and thus considers] its documents not final, but still open to discussion and amendment upon the convocation of the Great Pan-Orthodox Council in the presence and participation of all the Autocephalous Orthodox Churches.\"<ref name=\"antiochsynod2\">{{cite web|title=Statement of the Secretariat of the Holy Synod of Antioch, Balamand, 27 June 2016|url=http://antiochpatriarchate.org/en/page/1448/#English|website=Greek Orthodox Patriarchate of Antioch and All the East|accessdate=7 November 2017}}</ref>\n\n==== Russian Church ====\nThe [[Russian Orthodox Church]] pulled out because of her belief that the council is not truly \"pan-orthodox\" without the Antiochan, Bulgarian, or Georgian churches.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.firstthings.com/blogs/firstthoughts/2016/06/the-great-orthodox-council-antioch-is-different|title=The Great Orthodox Council: Antioch Is Different|last=Damick|first=Andrew Stephen|last2=Noble|first2=Samuel|date=20 June 2016|website=First Things|publisher=|access-date=12 August 2016}}</ref><ref>''[http://interfax-religion.com/?act=news&div=13017 Russian Church insists on rescheduling Pan-Orthodox Council].'' Interfax-Religion. 13 June 2016, 19:16.</ref> Previously, a preliminary discussion was held on the composition of the delegation to the Pan-Orthodox Council,<ref>''[https://mospat.ru/en/2016/05/04/news131113/ MINUTES OF THE HOLY SYNOD SESSION OF APRIL 16, 2016].'' The Russian orthodox Church - DECR. 04.05.2016 16:57.</ref> and the list of participants was published.<ref name=\"PATRIARCHIA-RU-MAY4\">{{in lang|ru}} ''[http://www.patriarchia.ru/db/text/4460239.html \u0416\u0423\u0420\u041d\u0410\u041b \u0437\u0430\u0441\u0435\u0434\u0430\u043d\u0438\u044f \u0421\u0432\u044f\u0449\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0421\u0438\u043d\u043e\u0434\u0430 \u043e\u0442 16 \u0430\u043f\u0440\u0435\u043b\u044f 2016 \u0433\u043e\u0434\u0430].'' Patriarchia.ru. 4 \u043c\u0430\u044f 2016 \u0433. 13:37.</ref>{{#tag:ref|The delegation of the Church of Russia that had been approved on May 4 had included the following bishops:<ref name=PATRIARCHIA-RU-MAY4/> \n* Patriarch [[Patriarch Kirill of Moscow|Kirill of Moscow]].\n* Metropolitan [[Onufriy (Berezovsky)]], of Kiev and All Ukraine.\n* Metropolitan [[Juvenal (Poyarkov)]] of Krutitsy and Kolomna.\n* Metropolitan [[Vladimir (Cantarean)]] of Kishinev and All Moldavia.\n* Metropolitan Alexander of Astana and Kazakhstan, head of the Metropolitan Region in the Republic of Kazakhstan.\n* Metropolitan Vikenty of Tashkent and Uzbekistan, head of the Central Asia Metropolitan Region.\n* Metropolitan Varsonofy of St Petersburg and Ladoga, chancellor of the Moscow Patriarchate.\n* Metropolitan [[Paul (Ponomaryov)]] of Minsk and Zaslavl, Patriarchal Exarch for All Belarus.\n* Metropolitan [[Hilarion (Alfeyev)]] of Volokolamsk, head of the Moscow Patriarchate department for external church relations.\n* Metropolitan Agafangel of Odessa and Izmail.\n* Metropolitan Alexander of Riga and All Latvia.\n* Metropolitan Tikhon of Novosibirsk and Berdsk.\n* Metropolitan Sergiy of Ternopol and Kremenets.\n* Metropolitan Kirill of Yekaterinburg and Verkhoturye.\n* Metropolitan [[Mercurius (Ivanov)]] of Rostov and Novocherkassk.\n* Metropolitan Mitrofan of Lugansk and Alchevsk, chairman of the Ukrainian Orthodox Church department for external church relations.\n* Metropolitan George (Danilov) of Niznniy Novrogod and Arzamas.\n* Metropolitan Anthony of Borispol and Brovary, chancellor of the Ukrainian Orthodox Church.\n* Archbishop [[Mark (Arndt)]] of Berlin-Germany and Great Britain.\n* Archbishop Innokenty of Vilna and Lithuania.\n* Archbishop Guriy of Novogrudok and Slonim.\n* Archbishop Seraphim of Sendai.\n* Archbishop Ioann of Magadan and Sinegorye.\n* Archbishop Lazar of Narva and Prichudje.\n* Bishop Anthony of Bogorodsk.|group=note}}\n\nIn 2007 the Moscow and Constantinople patriarchates disagreed at the [[Joint International Commission for Theological Dialogue Between the Catholic Church and the Orthodox Church]] over the issue of the [[Eastern Orthodoxy in Estonia|Estonian Church]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Russian delegates walk out of talks with Vatican over dispute with another Orthodox church|url=http://wwrn.org/articles/26546/?&place=europe&section=christianity|website=World-Wide Religious News|accessdate=5 January 2017|date=11 October 2007}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Position of the Moscow Patriarchate on the problem of primacy in the Universal Church|url=https://mospat.ru/en/2013/12/26/news96344/|website=The Russian Orthodox Church|accessdate=5 January 2017|date=26 December 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Lambriniadis|first1=Elpidophoros|title=First without equals: A response to the text on primacy of the Moscow Patriarchate|url=https://www.patriarchate.org/theological-and-other-studies/-/asset_publisher/GovONi6kIiut/content/primus-sine-paribus-hapantesis-eis-to-peri-proteiou-keimenon-tou-patriarcheiou-moschas-tou-sebasmiotatou-metropolitou-prouses-k-elpidophorou?inheritRedirect=false&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.patriarchate.org%2Ftheological-and-other-studies%3Fp_p_id%3D101_INSTANCE_GovONi6kIiut%26p_p_lifecycle%3D0%26p_p_state%3Dnormal%26p_p_mode%3Dview%26p_p_col_id%3Dcolumn-1%26p_p_col_pos%3D1%26p_p_col_count%3D2|website=The Ecumenical Patriarchate|accessdate=5 January 2017|date=2 December 2014}}</ref> [[Stephanos of Tallinn|Metropolitan Stephanos]], the primate of the [[Estonian Apostolic Orthodox Church|Constantinople-backed Estonian church]] attended with the Ecumenical Patriarch's Constantinopolitan delegation;<ref name=ConstDel /> [[Cornelius (Jakobs)|Metropolitan Cornelius]] of the [[Estonian Orthodox Church of Moscow Patriarchate|Russia-backed Estonian Church]] was not listed among the prospective Russian delegation.<ref name=PATRIARCHIA-RU-MAY4/>\n\n====Church of Bulgaria====\nThe [[Bulgarian Orthodox Church]] pulled out due to disagreements on some of the texts already approved for the Synod meeting, and specifically that those texts would not be subject to editing in the course of discussions, though that seemed to be a misunderstanding, since all documents were opened for discussion and other Churches went ready to and did amend them.<ref>Clive Leviev-Sawyer. ''[http://sofiaglobe.com/2016/06/01/bulgarian-orthodox-church-withdraws-from-pan-orthodox-council-in-crete/ Bulgarian Orthodox Church withdraws from Pan-Orthodox Council in Crete].'' The Sofia Globe. June 1, 2016.</ref>\n\n{{col-2}}\n\n====Church of Georgia====\nThe [[Georgian Orthodox Church]] pulled out due to disagreements about several of the Synod's documents, in particular \"The Relation of the Orthodox Church with the Rest of the Christian World\".<ref name=\"econo\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.interfax-religion.com/?act=news&div=13014|title=Georgian Church decides not to participate in Pan-Orthodox Council|last=|first=|date=10 June 2016|website=Interfax-Religion|publisher=|access-date=12 August 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2016 the holy synod of the Church of Georgia rejected the claim that the council, which it refers to as the \"Council of Crete\", was Pan Orthodox and the idea that its texts reflected Orthodox Teaching.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://orthodoxethos.com/post/final-decision-of-the-church-of-georgia-on-the-council-of-crete-summary |title=Final Decision of the Church of Georgia on the Council of Crete (SUMMARY) |website=OrthodoxEthos |date=27 December 2016 |access-date=4 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://patriarchate.ge/geo/wmida-sinodis-sxdomis-oqmi-22/ |title=\u10ec\u10db\u10d8\u10d3\u10d0 \u10e1\u10d8\u10dc\u10dd\u10d3\u10d8\u10e1 \u10e1\u10ee\u10d3\u10dd\u10db\u10d8\u10e1 \u10dd\u10e5\u10db\u10d8 |date=22 November 2016 |website=\u10e1\u10d0\u10e5\u10d0\u10e0\u10d7\u10d5\u10d4\u10da\u10dd\u10e1 \u10e1\u10d0\u10de\u10d0\u10e2\u10e0\u10d8\u10d0\u10e0\u10e5\u10dd |access-date=4 January 2017 |language=ka}}</ref>\n\n====Orthodox Church in America====\n\nThe [[Orthodox Church in America]] (OCA) was not invited due to the lack of recognition of her autocephaly by other autocephalous Churches. However, the jurisdiction did support the Council and its convocation by sending clergy scholars from among them to help with the event before, during, and after.{{Citation needed|date=March 2017}} In addition, she released an official letter in support of the Council and a special prayer to be included during every Divine Liturgy in every diocese.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Holy Synod of Bishops of the Orthodox Church in America|title=Holy Synod issues Statement, Petitions on the Holy and Great Council|url=https://oca.org/news/headline-news/holy-synod-issues-statement-petitions-on-the-holy-and-great-council|website=Orthodox Church in America|accessdate=30 March 2017|language=en|date=6 June 2016}}</ref> Also, OCA scholars were among the drafters of a special letter sent to every autocephalous Church urging them to support the convocation of the Council during the time when critical voices were pressuring certain Churches to not attend the synod just a few days before it was to meet.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Mavrick|first1=Nick|title=Over 1,000 Orthodox Scholars Urge the Council to be Held in June 2016|url=http://myocn.net/over-1000-orthodox-scholars-urge-the-council-to-be-held-in-june-2016/|website=Orthodox Christian Network|accessdate=30 March 2017|date=13 June 2016}}</ref> However, the OCA has not released a post-Council statement, and Metropolitan [[Tikhon Mollard|Tikhon]] has been in the process of resuming the discussion between the OCA and the Ecumenical Patriarchate.{{Citation needed|date=March 2017}}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|group=note}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Crete Council (2016)}}\n* '''''[https://www.holycouncil.org/ Official Website Of The Great And Holy Council]'''.''\n* '''''[https://www.orthodoxcouncil.org/# Comprehensive Information On The Great And Holy Council From The Ecumenical Patriarchate Featuring Information, News, Commentaries, And History Of The Council Under The Heading \"Road To The Council\"]'''.''\n* ''[https://www.orthodoxcouncil.org/home Ecumenical Patriarchate Press Office | Holy and Great Council of the Orthodox Church].'' The Ecumenical Patriarchate of Constantinople, 2016.\n* '' '''[https://www.facebook.com/groups/102830926814826/ Facebook Open Forum Dedicated to Information About the Council, Discussions, and The Future of Councils of the Orthodox Church Run By and With Participation of Clergy, Scholars, and Regular Laymen].''''''''\n* ''[https://publicorthodoxy.org/2016/05/17/on-consensus-a-canonical-appraisal/ Fr. Alexander Rentel On The Meaning Of Consensus].''\n* ''[https://www.youtube.com/watch?V=V5X3Iei1C7W Sister Vassa Can Non-Orthodox Be Called \"Churches\"?].''\n* ''[https://publicorthodoxy.org/2016/03/22/innovation-in-the-guise-of-tradition-anti-ecumenist-efforts-to-derail-the-grea