 to the Pan-Orthodox Council (2016): Signposts on the Way to Crete].'' \n* ''[http://www.pravoslavie.ru/english/92763.htm Bulgarian Orthodox Church: Outside The Orthodox Church \"There Are No Other Churches, Only Heresies And Schisms\"].''\n* ''[http://www.synod.com/synod/eng2016/20160413_ensynodposlaniye.html Communication of the Holy Synod of the Russian Orthodox Church Outside of Russia to the Clerics and Faithful].'' \n* ''[http://www.pravoslavie.ru/english/91211.htm Metropolitan Of New Smyrna: \"It Cannot Be Considered A Pan-Orthodox Council In Which Not Every Bishop Participates\"].'' \n* ''[http://www.pravoslavie.ru/english/90950.htm Video: Georgian Orthodox Church Rejects Document On Ecumenism Drafted For The Great Council, 2016].'' \n* Met. Hierotheos Vlachos. ''[http://www.pravoslavie.ru/english/90812.htm Letter To The Holy Synod Of Greece Concerning Preparations For The Upcoming Great And Holy Council].''\n* ''[http://www.pravoslavie.ru/english/90619.htm Metropolitan Of Limassol: \"What Unity Are We Talking About? Those Who Departed From The Church Are Heretics And Schismatics\"].''\n* ''[https://lessonsfromamonastery.wordpress.com/2016/02/09/professor-of-theology-dimitrios-tselingidis-observations-on-the-text-of-upcoming-council/ Dimitrios Tselingidis Observations on the Text of the Upcoming Council].''\n\n{{Ecumenical councils}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pan-Orthodox Council}}\n[[Category:Eastern Orthodox Church councils]]\n[[Category:2016 in Greece]]\n[[Category:21st-century Christian church councils]]\n", "name_user": "Dewritech", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eAgenda, decisions and reception:clean up,typo(s) fixed: \u2019s \u2192 's (3)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pan-Orthodox_Council"}
{"title_page": "Joohoney", "text_new": "{{short description|South Korean rapper}}\n{{Korean name|Lee}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name            = Joohoney\n| image           =171104 \uc8fc\ud5cc 02.jpg\n| caption         = Joohoney in November 2017\n| birth_name      = Lee Joo-heon\n| native_name     = \uc774\uc8fc\ud5cc\n| native_name_lang= kr\n| occupation      = {{hlist|[[Rapper]]|[[Songwriter]]}}\n| background      = solo_singer\n| genre           = {{hlist|[[K-pop]]|[[Hip hop music|hip hop]]}}\n| instrument      = Vocals\n| years_active    = 2015\u2013present\n| label           = [[Starship Entertainment|Starship]]\n| associated_acts = {{hlist|Nu Boyz|[[Monsta X]]}}\n| website         = http://monstax-e.com/\n| module          = {{Infobox Korean name|child=yes\n| title           = [[Korean name]]\n| hangul          = \uc774\uc8fc\ud5cc\n| hanja           =\n| rr              = I Juheon\n| mr              = Yi Chuh\u014fn\n}}}}\n\n'''Lee Joo-heon''' ([[Hangul]]: \uc774\uc8fc\ud5cc), better known by the stage name '''Joohoney''' (and formerly [[mononymous person|mononymously]]) is a South Korean rapper and songwriter. He is a member of South Korean [[boy group]] [[Monsta X]], which was formed through [[Mnet (TV channel)|Mnet]]'s survival show ''No.Mercy'' in 2015.\n\n==Career==\n===2014: Debut and career beginnings===\nPrior to his debut with Monsta X, Joohoney was part of a project group called Nu Boyz (along with #GUN, Shownu and Wonho) formed under [[Starship Entertainment]] in August 2014.<ref>{{cite web|title = [No Mercy] San E and Hyori feat. Joohoney 'Coach Me' announcement|url = http://news.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2015/01/03/2015010300418.html|website = Chosun|access-date = October 11, 2017}}</ref> The quartet uploaded multiple mixtapes to their company's [[YouTube]] channel<ref name=\"smtm4\">{{cite web|title = \uc8fc\ud5cc, \ubbf9\uc2a4\ud14c\uc78e \ubc1c\ub9e4\uc5d0 \uc774\uc5b4 '\uc1fc\ubbf8\ub354\uba38\ub2c84' \ucc38\uac00 '\uacb9\uacbd\uc0ac'|trans-title=Jooheon, Mix Tape, followed by 'Show Me Money 4' Participation '|url = http://news.joins.com/article/17699376|website = Korea Joongang Daily|access-date = October 11, 2017}}</ref> and performed at the opening show of Starship X concert in December 2014.<ref>{{cite web|title = \uac00\uc694\uacc4 \uc810\ub839\ud55c '\uc2a4\ud0c0\uc27dX', \uc62c\ub098\uc787 \ucf58\uc11c\ud2b8 12\uc6d4 5\uc77c \uac1c\ucd5c|trans-title='Starship X' occupied by the music industry, all night concert held on December 5, 2014|url = http://news.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2014/11/06/2014110600748.html|website = Chosun|access-date = October 10, 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2014, [[Starship Entertainment]] and [[Mnet (TV channel)|Mnet]] launched a competition program called ''No.Mercy''<ref name=\"no mercy\">{{cite news|title=JYP, Mnet team up to launch new girl group|work=[[The Korea Herald|Kpop Herald]]|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201502121718512474510_2&ACE_SEARCH=1|date=February 12, 2015|accessdate=July 11, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=New idol group to be born through Mnet's 'No Mercy'|work=Kpop Herald|first= Gyu-oh|last=Park|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201411131802564766044_2&ACE_SEARCH=1|date=November 13, 2014|accessdate=July 11, 2017}}</ref> and Jooheon was selected along with six other participants (including Shownu & Wonho) as part of [[Starship Entertainment]]'s new boy group [[Monsta X]] on the last episode of the show.<ref name=\"The Star Chosun\">{{cite news|title=\ubaac\uc2a4\ud0c0\uc5d1\uc2a4, \ub370\ubdd4 \ud654\ubcf4 \uc18d '\uac70\ub9ac\uc758 \uac70\uce5c \ubc18\ud56d\uc544' \ucf58\uc149\ud2b8 \ud654\uc81c!|trans-title=Monsta X, the debut picture of the 'wild rebel street' concept!|work=The Star Chosun|language=ko|url=http://thestar.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2015/05/07/2015050701065.html|date=May 7, 2015|accessdate=July 11, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170711022259/http://thestar.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2015/05/07/2015050701065.html|archive-date=July 11, 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n=== 2015\u2013present: ''Show Me the Money'' and solo activities ===\nIn January 2015, Joohoney released a collaboration track, \"Coach Me\", with [[San E]] and [[Sistar]]'s [[Hyolyn]].<ref name=\"coach\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/6429481/san-e-hyolyn-jooheon-coach-me-video-mv|title=Watch San E & Hyolyn's Sensual Collaboration 'Coach Me'|first=Jeff|last=Benjamin|date=June 1, 2015|work=Billboard|accessdate=February 28, 2017}}</ref> Joohoney and group member [[Yoo Ki-hyun|Kihyun]] also participated in the soundtrack for the South Korean drama ''[[Orange Marmalade (TV series)|Orange Marmalade]]'' for the song titled \"Attractable Woman\", which was released in May, 2015 and produced by Crazy Park and his team.<ref name=\"orange\">{{cite web |title=MONSTA X To Sing 'Orange Marmalade' OST|publisher=BNT News|first=You-bin|last= Ha|url=http://www.bntnews.co.uk/app/news.php?nid=20500|date=April 20, 2015|accessdate=July 11, 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn summer 2015, Joohoney auditioned for the fourth season of [[Mnet (TV channel)|Mnet]]'s rap competition series, ''[[Show Me the Money (South Korean TV series)|Show Me the Money]]''.<ref name=\"smtm4\"/> He made it to the third round, where he was eliminated in a 1-on-1 battle against rapper Lee Hyun-joon<ref>{{cite news|title='\uc1fc\ubbf8\ub354\uba38\ub2c84' \ubaac\uc2a4\ud0c0 \uc5d1\uc2a4 \uc8fc\ud5cc, \uc774\ud604\uc900 \uc0c1\ub300\ub85c \ucda9\uaca9\uc758 \ud0c8\ub77d|trans-title=SMTM4, Monsta X Jooheon, face against Lee Hyun-joon, shocking elimination|work=TV Report via Naver|url=http://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=213&aid=0000722522&gid=999339&cid=1004550|date=July 10, 2015|accessdate=July 11, 2017}}</ref> however he was later brought back for a second chance where he lost to [[One (rapper)|One]].<ref>{{cite news|title='\uc1fc\ubbf8\ub354\uba38\ub2c84' \ubc15\uc7ac\ubc94 \"\uc6d0\ud380\uce58 \uc6d0\u00b7\ubaac\uc2a4\ud0c0\uc5d1\uc2a4 \uc8fc\ud5cc, \uacbd\uc7c1 \uce58\uc5f4\ud574\"\u2026 \uc6d0, \uc8fc\ud5cc \uc81c\ucce4\ub2e4 (\uae08\uc694\uc77c \uc608\ub2a5)|trans-title=SMTM4, \"One-Punch Won \u00b7 Monsta X Jooheon, Competition ...\" Won, won the judes|work=News Inside|url=http://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=213&aid=0000722522&gid=999339&cid=1004550|date=July 10, 2015|accessdate=July 11, 2017|author=Kim Jong-ran}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, he was one of the producers for [[JTBC]]'s hip-hop competition show ''[[Tribe of Hip Hop]]''.<ref name=\"tribeofhiphop\">{{cite web|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20160330000866|title=Grannies grab the mic on 'Tribe of Hiphop'|date=March 30, 2016|accessdate=February 28, 2017|author=Jung Eun-jin|quote=The producers include hip-hop stars P-type, Jooheon, Lil Boi, KittiB, Cheetah, DinDin, Hanhae and MC Sniper.}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, he released a solo MV with the song \u201cRhythm\u201d.\n\nIn 2018, August 31, he released his first official mixtape \u201cDWTD\u201d.<ref>https://open.spotify.com/album/6KkarMWzWu5QwznlQeloZE?si=1O7VOKr-Tm6l_XFBmzF45w Spotify. Retrieved September 6, 2019.</ref> Along with a MV for the track \u201cRed Carpet\u201d. A few months later in October he released a second MV, this time for the track \u201cShould I Do\u201d.\n\nIn February 2019, he changed his stage name from Jooheon to Joohoney.<ref>{{cite web|title=\uc555\ub3c4\uc801 \ub0a8\uc131\u7f8e\"..\ubaac\uc2a4\ud0c0\uc5d1\uc2a4\uc758 \ub2e4\ud06c \uce74\ub9ac\uc2a4\ub9c8[Oh!\uc388 \ucef7]|language=ko|work=OSEN|accessdate=March 31, 2019|url=http://osen.mt.co.kr/article/G1111078123|last=Sung|first=Mi-kyung|date=February 8, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn January 11, 2020, Jooheon took a temporarily break from Monsta X in order to focus on his mental health. He continued promotions again late March 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/international/8547869/monsta-xs-joohoney-hiatus-mental-health|title=Monsta X's Joohoney Announces Hiatus to Focus on Mental Health|last=Herman|first=Tamar|date=January 13, 2020|website=Billboard|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n== Discography ==\n=== As lead artist ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n! Year\n! Song Title\n! Album\n! Artist\n! Ref.\n|-\n| 2015\n| \"Interstellar\"\n| ''[[Trespass (EP)|Trespass]]''\n| with Hyungwon and I.M ([[Monsta X]]) <small>feat. Yella Diamond</small>\n| <ref name=\"The Star Chosun\"/>\n|}\n\n=== As featured artist ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n! Year\n! Song Title\n! Album\n! Artist\n! Ref.\n|-\n| 2014\n| \"Ganggab\" (\uae7d\uac12)\n| ''Pyodok''\n| [[Mad Clown]]\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 2015\n| \"Coach Me\"\n| ''No.Mercy'' OST Part 1\n| [[Hyolyn]] ([[Sistar]]) and [[San E]]\n| <ref name=\"coach\"/>\n|-\n| \"0 (Young)\"\n| ''No.Mercy'' OST Part 3\n| [[Jooyoung]], Mad Clown and [[Giriboy]]\n| <ref>{{cite web |title='\ub178\uba38\uc2dc', \uc624\ub298(5\uc77c) \ub9e4\ub4dc\ud074\ub77c\uc6b4X\uc8fc\uc601 '0' \uc74c\uc6d0 \uacf5\uac1c|trans-title='No Mercy' Mad Clown releases collaboration with No.Mercy contestants|publisher=Top Star News|author=Woo Sun |url=http://www.topstarnews.net/detail.php?number=103851|date=February 5, 2015|accessdate=July 11, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| \"Bad X\"\n| rowspan=\"4\" {{N/A|Non-album singles}}\n| [[J'Kyun]] and Konsoul\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2016\n| \"H.ear Your Colors\"\n| Mad Clown\n|\n|-\n| \"Slow\"\n| Hyolyn (Sistar)\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201611081313115986802_2|title=[V Report] Hyolyn, Monsta X Jooheon show chemistry in 'Slow'|website=Kpop Herald|accessdate=November 8, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2019\n| \"Ongsimi\" (\uc639\uc2ec\uc774)\n| Minhyuk (Monsta X)\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.upi.com/Entertainment_News/Music/2019/06/28/Monsta-X-member-Minhyuk-releases-Ongsimi-mixtape-music-video/6551561741359/|title=Monsta X member Minhyuk releases 'Ongsimi' mixtape, music video|author=Annie Martin (June 28, 2019)|work=[[United Press International|UPI]]|accessdate=June 29, 2019}}</ref>\n|}\n\n=== Soundtrack appearances ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n! Year\n! Song Title\n! Album\n! Artist\n! Ref.\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2015\n| \"Attracted Woman\"\n| ''[[Orange Marmalade (TV series)|Orange Marmalade]]'' OST\n| with [[Yoo Ki-hyun|Kihyun]] (Monsta X)\n| <ref name=\"orange\"/>\n|-\n| \"Similar\"\n| ''[[Mask (2015 TV series)|Mask]]'' OST Part 7\n| with [[Junggigo]]\n| <ref>{{cite web|last1=|first1=|title=Melon album details (Mask OST Part 7) |url=http://www.melon.com/album/detail.htm?albumId=2328118|website=Melon|publisher=|accessdate=October 15, 2017|language=Korean}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2018\n| \"Can't Breathe\"\n| ''[[Investigation Couple]]'' OST Part 1\n| with Kihyun (Monsta X)\n| <ref>{{cite web|last1=|first1=|title=Monsta X Kihyun and Jooheon participates in OST of 'Men and Women of the guards ...' 'Can not Breathe' release 21 May|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=076&aid=0003259295|website=Naver|publisher=|accessdate=May 21, 2018|language=Korean}}</ref>\n|}\n\n=== Mixtapes ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n! Year\n! Song Title\n! Mixtape Title\n! Ref.\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 2015\n| \"Get Low\" <small>feat. Mad Clown</small>\n| rowspan=\"2\"|SUPEXX\n| rowspan=\"2\"|<ref>{{cite web|title = Music Naver - SUPEXX, artist \uc8fc\ud5cc (JOOHEON) and \ub9e4\ub4dc \ud074\ub77c\uc6b4(Mad Clown)|url = http://music.naver.com/album/index.nhn?albumId=558963|website = Naver Music|access-date = October 10, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| \"Stay Strong\" <small>feat. [[Flowsik]]</small>\n|-\n| \"Flower Cafe\" <small>feat. I.M (Monsta X) & Sam Ock</small>\n| Flower Cafe\n| <ref>{{cite web|title = Music Naver - Flower Cafe, artist \uc8fc\ud5cc (JOOHEON)|url = http://music.naver.com/album/index.nhn?albumId=597143|website = Naver Music|access-date = October 10, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2017\n| \"Be My Friend\" <small>with I.M (Monsta X)</small>\n| {{N/A|Non-album single}}\n|\n|-\n| 2018\n| \"Red Carpet\"\n| DWTD\n| <ref>{{cite web|title = Spotify - DTWD, artist \uc8fc\ud5cc (JOOHEON)|url = http://open.spotify.com/album/6KkarMWzWu5QwznlQeloZE|website = Spotify|access-date = August 31, 2018}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== Filmography ==\n=== TV appearances ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n!Year\n!Network\n!Show\n!Role\n!Ref.\n|-\n| 2014\u20132015\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[Mnet (TV channel)|Mnet]]\n| ''No.Mercy''\n| rowspan=\"2\"| Contestant\n| <ref name=\"no mercy\"/>\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''[[Show Me the Money 4]]''\n| <ref name=\"smtm4\"/>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 2016\n| [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBig TV]]\n| ''[[Celebrity Bromance]]''\n| Cast member with [[Jackson Wang|Jackson]] ([[GOT7]])\n| <ref>{{cite web|last1=Choi|first1=Jin-sil|title=\uac13\uc138\ube10 \uc7ad\uc2a8\u00b7\ubaac\uc2a4\ud0c0\uc5d1\uc2a4 \uc8fc\ud5cc, '\uaf43\ubbf8\ub0a8 \ube0c\ub85c\ub9e8\uc2a4' \ud569\ub958 |url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=311&aid=0000598635|website=Naver|publisher=|accessdate=October 15, 2017|language=Korean|trans-title=GOT7\u2019s Jackson and MONSTA X\u2019s Jooheon join \u201cCelebrity Bromance\u201d}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[JTBC]]\n| ''[[Tribe of Hip Hop|Tribe Of Hip Hop]]''\n| Producer\n| <ref name=\"tribeofhiphop\"/>\n|-\n| [[MBC Every1]]\n| ''[[Weekly Idol]]''\n| Co-host\n| <ref>{{cite web|last1=Kim|first1=Hyun-jeong|title='\uc8fc\uac04\uc544\uc774\ub3cc' \uc7ad\uc2a8\u00b7\ub2e4\ud604\u00b7\uc2e0\ube44\u00b7\uc8fc\ud5cc, '\uc544\uc774\ub3ccis\ubb54\ub4e4' \ud569\ub958|trans-title=\"Weekly Idol\" Jooheon, Jackson, Dahyun and SinB join new segment|url=http://www.xportsnews.com/jenter/?ac=article_view&entry_id=710685|website=XSportsNews|publisher=|accessdate=April 6, 2016|language=Korean}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2019\n| [[Mnet (TV channel)|Mnet]]\n| ''[[Produce X 101]]''\n| Battle Rap Trainer\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.soompi.com/article/1327137wpp/monsta-xs-joohoney-and-park-sun-ho-tearfully-reunite-on-produce-x-101|title=MONSTA X's Joohoney And Park Sun Ho Tearfully Reunite On 'Produce X 101'|website=[[Soompi]]|accessdate=May 26, 2019}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Monsta X}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Joohoney}}\n[[Category:1994 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Starship Entertainment artists]]\n[[Category:South Korean male idols]]\n[[Category:South Korean male rappers]]\n[[Category:South Korean pop singers]]\n[[Category:South Korean singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:Show Me the Money (South Korean TV series) contestants]]\n[[Category:Weekly Idol members]]\n[[Category:Rappers from Seoul]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|South Korean rapper}}\n{{Korean name|Lee}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name            = Joohoney\n| image           =171104 \uc8fc\ud5cc 02.jpg\n| caption         = Joohoney in November 2017\n| birth_name      = Lee Joo-heon\n| native_name     = \uc774\uc8fc\ud5cc\n| native_name_lang= kr\n| occupation      = {{hlist|[[Rapper]]|[[Songwriter]]}}\n| background      = solo_singer\n| genre           = {{hlist|[[K-pop]]|[[Hip hop music|hip hop]]}}\n| instrument      = Vocals\n| years_active    = 2015\u2013present\n| label           = [[Starship Entertainment|Starship]]\n| associated_acts = {{hlist|Nu Boyz|[[Monsta X]]}}\n| website         = http://monstax-e.com/\n| module          = {{Infobox Korean name|child=yes\n| title           = [[Korean name]]\n| hangul          = \uc774\uc8fc\ud5cc\n| hanja           =\n| rr              = I Juheon\n| mr              = Yi Chuh\u014fn\n}}}}\n\n'''Lee Joo-heon''' ([[Hangul]]: \uc774\uc8fc\ud5cc), better known by the stage name '''Joohoney''' (and formerly [[mononymous person|mononymously]]) is a South Korean rapper and songwriter. He is a member of South Korean [[boy group]] [[Monsta X]], which was formed through [[Mnet (TV channel)|Mnet]]'s survival show ''No.Mercy'' in 2015.\n\n==Career==\n===2014: Debut and career beginnings===\nPrior to his debut with Monsta X, Joohoney was part of a project group called Nu Boyz (along with #GUN, Shownu and Wonho) formed under [[Starship Entertainment]] in August 2014.<ref>{{cite web|title = [No Mercy] San E and Hyori feat. Joohoney 'Coach Me' announcement|url = http://news.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2015/01/03/2015010300418.html|website = Chosun|access-date = October 11, 2017}}</ref> The quartet uploaded multiple mixtapes to their company's [[YouTube]] channel<ref name=\"smtm4\">{{cite web|title = \uc8fc\ud5cc, \ubbf9\uc2a4\ud14c\uc78e \ubc1c\ub9e4\uc5d0 \uc774\uc5b4 '\uc1fc\ubbf8\ub354\uba38\ub2c84' \ucc38\uac00 '\uacb9\uacbd\uc0ac'|trans-title=Jooheon, Mix Tape, followed by 'Show Me Money 4' Participation '|url = http://news.joins.com/article/17699376|website = Korea Joongang Daily|access-date = October 11, 2017}}</ref> and performed at the opening show of Starship X concert in December 2014.<ref>{{cite web|title = \uac00\uc694\uacc4 \uc810\ub839\ud55c '\uc2a4\ud0c0\uc27dX', \uc62c\ub098\uc787 \ucf58\uc11c\ud2b8 12\uc6d4 5\uc77c \uac1c\ucd5c|trans-title='Starship X' occupied by the music industry, all night concert held on December 5, 2014|url = http://news.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2014/11/06/2014110600748.html|website = Chosun|access-date = October 10, 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2014, [[Starship Entertainment]] and [[Mnet (TV channel)|Mnet]] launched a competition program called ''No.Mercy''<ref name=\"no mercy\">{{cite news|title=JYP, Mnet team up to launch new girl group|work=[[The Korea Herald|Kpop Herald]]|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201502121718512474510_2&ACE_SEARCH=1|date=February 12, 2015|accessdate=July 11, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=New idol group to be born through Mnet's 'No Mercy'|work=Kpop Herald|first= Gyu-oh|last=Park|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201411131802564766044_2&ACE_SEARCH=1|date=November 13, 2014|accessdate=July 11, 2017}}</ref> and Jooheon was selected along with six other participants (including Shownu & Wonho) as part of [[Starship Entertainment]]'s new boy group [[Monsta X]] on the last episode of the show.<ref name=\"The Star Chosun\">{{cite news|title=\ubaac\uc2a4\ud0c0\uc5d1\uc2a4, \ub370\ubdd4 \ud654\ubcf4 \uc18d '\uac70\ub9ac\uc758 \uac70\uce5c \ubc18\ud56d\uc544' \ucf58\uc149\ud2b8 \ud654\uc81c!|trans-title=Monsta X, the debut picture of the 'wild rebel street' concept!|work=The Star Chosun|language=ko|url=http://thestar.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2015/05/07/2015050701065.html|date=May 7, 2015|accessdate=July 11, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170711022259/http://thestar.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2015/05/07/2015050701065.html|archive-date=July 11, 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n=== 2015\u2013present: ''Show Me the Money'' and solo activities ===\nIn January 2015, Joohoney released a collaboration track, \"Coach Me\", with [[San E]] and [[Sistar]]'s [[Hyolyn]].<ref name=\"coach\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/6429481/san-e-hyolyn-jooheon-coach-me-video-mv|title=Watch San E & Hyolyn's Sensual Collaboration 'Coach Me'|first=Jeff|last=Benjamin|date=June 1, 2015|work=Billboard|accessdate=February 28, 2017}}</ref> Joohoney and group member [[Yoo Ki-hyun|Kihyun]] also participated in the soundtrack for the South Korean drama ''[[Orange Marmalade (TV series)|Orange Marmalade]]'' for the song titled \"Attractable Woman\", which was released in May, 2015 and produced by Crazy Park and his team.<ref name=\"orange\">{{cite web |title=MONSTA X To Sing 'Orange Marmalade' OST|publisher=BNT News|first=You-bin|last= Ha|url=http://www.bntnews.co.uk/app/news.php?nid=20500|date=April 20, 2015|accessdate=July 11, 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn summer 2015, Joohoney auditioned for the fourth season of [[Mnet (TV channel)|Mnet]]'s rap competition series, ''[[Show Me the Money (South Korean TV series)|Show Me the Money]]''.<ref name=\"smtm4\"/> He made it to the third round, where he was eliminated in a 1-on-1 battle against rapper Lee Hyun-joon<ref>{{cite news|title='\uc1fc\ubbf8\ub354\uba38\ub2c84' \ubaac\uc2a4\ud0c0 \uc5d1\uc2a4 \uc8fc\ud5cc, \uc774\ud604\uc900 \uc0c1\ub300\ub85c \ucda9\uaca9\uc758 \ud0c8\ub77d|trans-title=SMTM4, Monsta X Jooheon, face against Lee Hyun-joon, shocking elimination|work=TV Report via Naver|url=http://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=213&aid=0000722522&gid=999339&cid=1004550|date=July 10, 2015|accessdate=July 11, 2017}}</ref> however he was later brought back for a second chance where he lost to [[One (rapper)|One]].<ref>{{cite news|title='\uc1fc\ubbf8\ub354\uba38\ub2c84' \ubc15\uc7ac\ubc94 \"\uc6d0\ud380\uce58 \uc6d0\u00b7\ubaac\uc2a4\ud0c0\uc5d1\uc2a4 \uc8fc\ud5cc, \uacbd\uc7c1 \uce58\uc5f4\ud574\"\u2026 \uc6d0, \uc8fc\ud5cc \uc81c\ucce4\ub2e4 (\uae08\uc694\uc77c \uc608\ub2a5)|trans-title=SMTM4, \"One-Punch Won \u00b7 Monsta X Jooheon, Competition ...\" Won, won the judes|work=News Inside|url=http://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=213&aid=0000722522&gid=999339&cid=1004550|date=July 10, 2015|accessdate=July 11, 2017|author=Kim Jong-ran}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, he was one of the producers for [[JTBC]]'s hip-hop competition show ''[[Tribe of Hip Hop]]''.<ref name=\"tribeofhiphop\">{{cite web|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20160330000866|title=Grannies grab the mic on 'Tribe of Hiphop'|date=March 30, 2016|accessdate=February 28, 2017|author=Jung Eun-jin|quote=The producers include hip-hop stars P-type, Jooheon, Lil Boi, KittiB, Cheetah, DinDin, Hanhae and MC Sniper.}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, he released a solo MV with the song \u201cRhythm\u201d.\n\nIn 2018, August 31, he released his first official mixtape \u201cDWTD\u201d.<ref>https://open.spotify.com/album/6KkarMWzWu5QwznlQeloZE?si=1O7VOKr-Tm6l_XFBmzF45w Spotify. Retrieved September 6, 2019.</ref> Along with a MV for the track \u201cRed Carpet\u201d. A few months later in October he released a second MV, this time for the track \u201cShould I Do\u201d.\n\nIn February 2019, he changed his stage name from Jooheon to Joohoney.<ref>{{cite web|title=\uc555\ub3c4\uc801 \ub0a8\uc131\u7f8e\"..\ubaac\uc2a4\ud0c0\uc5d1\uc2a4\uc758 \ub2e4\ud06c \uce74\ub9ac\uc2a4\ub9c8[Oh!\uc388 \ucef7]|language=ko|work=OSEN|accessdate=March 31, 2019|url=http://osen.mt.co.kr/article/G1111078123|last=Sung|first=Mi-kyung|date=February 8, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn January 11, 2020, Jooheon took a temporarily break from Monsta X in order to focus on his mental health. He continued promotions again late March 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/international/8547869/monsta-xs-joohoney-hiatus-mental-health|title=Monsta X's Joohoney Announces Hiatus to Focus on Mental Health|last=Herman|first=Tamar|date=January, 13, 2020|website=Billboard|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n== Discography ==\n=== As lead artist ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n! Year\n! Song Title\n! Album\n! Artist\n! Ref.\n|-\n| 2015\n| \"Interstellar\"\n| ''[[Trespass (EP)|Trespass]]''\n| with Hyungwon and I.M ([[Monsta X]]) <small>feat. Yella Diamond</small>\n| <ref name=\"The Star Chosun\"/>\n|}\n\n=== As featured artist ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n! Year\n! Song Title\n! Album\n! Artist\n! Ref.\n|-\n| 2014\n| \"Ganggab\" (\uae7d\uac12)\n| ''Pyodok''\n| [[Mad Clown]]\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 2015\n| \"Coach Me\"\n| ''No.Mercy'' OST Part 1\n| [[Hyolyn]] ([[Sistar]]) and [[San E]]\n| <ref name=\"coach\"/>\n|-\n| \"0 (Young)\"\n| ''No.Mercy'' OST Part 3\n| [[Jooyoung]], Mad Clown and [[Giriboy]]\n| <ref>{{cite web |title='\ub178\uba38\uc2dc', \uc624\ub298(5\uc77c) \ub9e4\ub4dc\ud074\ub77c\uc6b4X\uc8fc\uc601 '0' \uc74c\uc6d0 \uacf5\uac1c|trans-title='No Mercy' Mad Clown releases collaboration with No.Mercy contestants|publisher=Top Star News|author=Woo Sun |url=http://www.topstarnews.net/detail.php?number=103851|date=February 5, 2015|accessdate=July 11, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| \"Bad X\"\n| rowsp