n]] (town proper) of El Nido. This concrete airstrip is owned and operated by [[AirSWIFT]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Air Swift|url=http://air-swift.com/}}</ref> The gravel runway is now partially coated and used as a taxiway for aircraft.\n\n==Airlines and destinations==\n{{Airport-dest-list\n|[[AirSWIFT]]| [[Francisco B. Reyes Airport|Busuanga]],  [[Godofredo P. Ramos Airport|Caticlan]], [[Mactan-Cebu International Airport|Cebu]], [[Clark International Airport|Clark]], [[Ninoy Aquino International Airport|Manila]], [[Puerto Princesa International Airport|Puerto Princesa]], [[Bohol\u2013Panglao International Airport|Tagbilaran]]<ref>{{cite news|last=Liu|first=Jim|date=16 March 2020|title=Filipino carriers Manila cancellations 15MAR20 \u2013 14APR20|url=https://www.routesonline.com/news/38/airlineroute/290316/filipino-carriers-manila-cancellations-15mar20-14apr20/|work=Routesonline|accessdate=17 March 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n==External links==\n* {{ASN|ENI}}\n\n<!--Navigation box--><br />\n{{Airports in the Philippines|state=collapsed}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Airports in the Philippines]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Palawan]]\n", "text_old": "{{Redirect|Lio Airport|the airport in Costa Rica with IATA code LIO|Lim\u00f3n International Airport}}\n{{Infobox airport\n| name = El Nido Airport\n| nativename = <small> ''Hulugpaan sang El Nido'' (Hiligaynon) <br> ''Paliparan ng El Nido'' (Filipino)</small>\n| image = El Nido Airport, 2005-03-28.jpg\n| caption = Apron of El Nido Airport\n| IATA = ENI\n| ICAO = \n| type = Private\n| owner = [[AirSWIFT]]\n| operator = Ten Knots Development Corp.\n| city-served = [[El Nido, Palawan|El Nido]]\n| location = Villa Libertad, El Nido, [[Palawan]]\n| elevation-f = \n| elevation-m = \n| metric-elev = yes\n| coordinates = {{coord|11|12|07|N|119|25|01|E|display=inline, title}}\n| pushpin_map = Philippines\n| pushpin_label = ENI\n| pushpin_map_caption = Location in the Philippines\n| r